- This is a TypeScript ESM library for privacy-preserving Web of Trust on Nostr
- British English throughout (licence, serialise, initialise)
- All local imports use .js extensions
- Types live in types.ts within each module directory (nip85, proof, identity)
- Tests mirror source: test/nip85/, test/proof/, test/identity/
- TDD: write the failing test first, then implement
- Commits: type: description (feat:, fix:, docs:, test:)
- Noble v2 requires Uint8Array not hex strings — use hexToBytes() before noble calls
- The _noble-compat.ts shim wraps schnorr for hex string support — don't remove without updating call sites
- contributeAssertion needs the member's 0-based index in circle.members (sorted pubkey order)
- aggregateContributions validates all LSAG sigs before aggregating — invalid sigs throw, not silently drop
- The demo app in demo/ is a separate Vite project with its own package.json
- Build: npm run build | Test: npm test | Lint: npm run lint | Demo: npm run demo
